MapCSS is a CSS-like language for map stylesheets. This repository handles the specification. Feel free to raise an issue or suggest an improvement by creating a pull request.

* [http://www.mapcss.org/ MapCSS website]
* [http://lists.openstreetmap.org/listinfo/mapcss MapCSS Mailing list at mapcss@openstreetmap.org]

* [[specification.mediawiki|Specification]]

== List of software supporting MapCSS ==
* [[Halcyon]] (flash-based renderer)
* [[Kothic]] (python/cairo based renderer, regexp-based parser)
* [[Ceyx]] (python/cairo based renderer)
* [[Potlatch]] (online flash-based editor)
* [[JOSM]] (offline Java-based editor; [https://help.openstreetmap.org/questions/22384/highlight-untagged-and-unconnected-nodes-in-a-way example])
* [[Kothic JS]] (javascript/HTML5-based renderer)
* [[Komap]] (mapnik stylesheet preprocessor)
* [[Tcl-OSM]] (parser)
* [https://github.com/Gubaer/dart-mapcss dart-mapcss] - provides an [http://www.antlr.org/ antlr] grammar for MapCSS and a generated lexer/parser in googles [http://www.dartlang.org Dart] programming language
* [[overpass turbo#Styling|overpass turbo]] (data mining tool based on Overpass API) [http://www.openstreetmap.org/user/tyr_asd/diary/19043 More information]
* [https://github.com/plepe/pgmapcss PGMapCSS] (Runtime CSS evaluation in PostgreSQL; for use with Mapnik)
